blocks.text: We watch heavy storm clouds as we lunch at Big Bend.

Big Bend National Park - W-Texas
It is a triangle formed by the
Rio Grande, which runs South,
then north in a big bend and
flows through deep canyons,
notably the South Hélene Canyon.

blocks.text: We drive through NW corner of Georgia to stop in Chattanooga, Tenn. to visit Dawson and Dorothy King (Richard King's parents)

Copperhill - an area where nothing grows - it seems very dead due to Sulphur fumes. also Ducktown is the same.
In the small town N.C. stands this marble courthouse. We visited the quarry located here.

In the small town, Murphy N.C. stands this all marble courthouse.
We visited the marble quarry located here.
